#AD You know how good it feels when someone gives you a compliment? I know it puts a smile on my face. Ha. 

So, I decided to pay that feeling forward, and today I went and passed out compliments to strangers at PCM for the @truist #12DaysofCare challenge. And everyone passed the vibe check — it totally made their day. 

With everything going on during this season, spreading joy and positivity can go a long way, and that’s exactly what this challenge is about. 

So now I’m inviting you to join me as well. Do good and show care. #TimeforCare

There’s nothing better than spending quality time with your friends and loved ones, especially over a great meal. #ad

That’s exactly why I’m excited to continue my partnership with @Truist this year for the #12DaysofCare challenge. Today, I asked some of my homies to pull up for brunch and we broke bread and just enjoyed the good vibes together. 

This holiday season, let’s commit to slowing down for a minute and showing care for the ones that mean the most to us. 

Hit the comments and let me know how you’ll celebrate your friends this season. #TimeforCare

Legacy building is important to us and that’s exactly why we created our family trust. 

Here’s how we did it:

1️⃣ Consultated with our Estate Planning Attorney:  She assesed our situation, discussed our goals, and provided legal advice tailored to our family’s needs.

2️⃣ Drafted the Trust Document: We worked closely with our attorney to outline the specific terms of the trust, including assets and beneficiaries, and then the trust document was prepared.

3️⃣ Funded and Executed Trust: After the trust document was finalized, we then will transfer ownership of our assets into the trust making the trust the new owners. 

Legacy building has to start somewhere and it’s important to us that we’re intentional about leaving an inheritance for Tatum, Maxwell, and their children’s children. 💯

Shoutout to our estate planning attorney, @askattorneyali, for a smooth and informative process. 

Drop a ❤️ if you believe in building a family legacy.
——
#trustfundbaby #familytrust #estateplanningattorney

There’s no manual to parenting but at the very least, we gon try our hardest to make sure our kids are good-hearted people. ❤️
Here’s how we do it:

1. Model loving & healthy relationships at home. 
2. Promote empathy, gratitude, and kindness. 
3. Teach resilence by showing how to get back up each time they fall.
4. Engage them with chores around the house. 
5. Protect their energy from vibes/people we’re not aligned with. 
6. Pray together. 

Drop a ❤️ if you believe we need to raise more good-hearted humans. 
——
#parentinghacks #goodhumans #RaisingTatum #RaisingMaxwell

#AD Black health is Black joy. As I approach 40 in a few years, prostate cancer awareness hits different. Why? Because 40 is the recommended age for Black men to begin screening for prostate cancer. It’s important and we just aren’t talking about it out loud enough, which is why I’m excited to team up with #Janssen to #TalkThatTalk

The fact is that 1 in 6 Black men will be diagnosed with prostate cancer. But if screened regularly and detected early, the survival rate increases.

So, fellas, let’s express our individual Black Boy Joy through our health - by learning family health history and discussing prostate screenings with our doctors.

Hit the link in my bio for more info on prostate cancer and tips for how to have those conversations with your doctor. Let’s get it!

#TalkThatTalkTime #TalkThatTalkPC #BlackMensHealth #ProstateCancer

#Sponsored Fitness has become an integral part of my life as of late and I use my legs every day, so I can’t imagine having to amputate one.
 
Well, that’s the case for a lot of people who have PAD or peripheral artery disease. It’s basically an often-underdiagnosed condition from heart disease where cholesterol build up blocks blood flow to your limbs – which often leads to amputations. And it’s especially impacting our Black community at 4x the rate than our white counterparts.
 
I’m partnering with Janssen for its Save Legs. Change Lives. initiative so that one, we can make healthier choices, but also two, to understand the risks as well as family history to prevent this from happening.
 
Hit the link in my bio to learn more.
#SaveLegsChangeLives
